    "This study was approved by the Western Institutional Review Board.",
    "All participants provided written informed consent prior to completion of the study protocol, in accordance with the Declaration of Helsinki, and were compensated for participation.",
    "ClinicalTrials.gov identifier: #NCT02450240.",
    "Data were collected from 500 participants (153 male) as a part of the Tulsa 1000 (T1000) project, a naturalistic longitudinal study that recruited subjects based on the dimensional NIMH Research Domain Criteria framework (a full description of this pre-planned project can be found in [64]).",
    "Individuals aged 18-55 years were screened on the basis of dimensional psychopathology scores."
  ],
